item.title: Please Help! (List) [You Probarly Can Help]
item.dc:creator: @Continue Continue
item.description:
@Continue wrote:

Log in onto your source and do this:

::mypos

It will then give you this:

X = 4444, Y = 4543

The 4444 and 4543 are just random numbers. Whatever it says for you, you search for it. So, if mine said the above, I’d go into my client class and search for this:

4444

If I see something like this:

teleToX = 4444; teleToY = 4543;

Then I know that’s where my starting point is. Now you can change that to whatever you like. If you see this multiple times:

teleToX = 4444; teleToY = 4543;

Then it must be the starting, and death position or more. Change them and see what you can get out of them.
